divs: Sighting DetailsI live in Kent on East Hill. My place is in the landing pattern for aircraft coming and going from Seattle airport. However last night while stargazing on my back deck I got a glimpse of a bright light. Just as I was turning my head I observed a light that was in the southern ski and vary bright! Not your typical landing light from aircraft. As soon as I saw the light and realized it was out of place it imploded in and was gone! I didn���t observe any lights in the area from where it was to associate it to an aircraft, no flashing strobes nothing, it was just gone. Also, before the sighting I thought I saw a bright light just in the corner of my eye. As I would turn my head it would be gone! Did anyone else see this light? Rob
